---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Brutenis">
  <h1 class="text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-yarn-coral mb-8">About</h1>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
    Hi! I'm Brutenis, a computer scientist passionate about the visual side of computing — games, graphics, simulations, and anything that moves.
    </p>
    <p>
      I studied computer science at the University of Rostock, where I also did my
      <a href="/projects/automatic-bronchus-classification-bachelor-thesis">bachelor's thesis on bronchus classification</a>
      and my <a href="/projects/spine-segmentation-master-thesis">master's thesis on spine segmentation</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm also quite competitive, having participated in:
      <ul>
        <li>Over a hundred competitive programming competitions, most on <a href="https://codeforces.com/profile/LiquidFun">codeforces</a>. In recent years I have started organizing <a href="https://github.com/LiquidFun/FSR-Coding-Cup-2023">my own competitive programming competitions</a> and have joined the Germany-wide club <a href="https://cpulm.org/">CPUlm</a>. Together, we have organized multiple Germany-wide competitions, as well as the <a href="https://2025.nwerc.eu/">NWERC 2025</a>, which had over 600 participants from 12 countries.</li>
        <li>Over a dozen game jams, some highlights are on the <a href="/games">games</a> page</li>
        <li>A couple of <a href="/ctf">CTF (capture the flag) security challenges</a></li>
        <li>A couple of App Days and Hackathons, with the most notable being the <a href="https://www.healthcarehackathon-mv.de/">MV Healthcare Hackathon</a> where we submitted <a href="https://github.com/LiquidFun/medico-mv">Medico-MV</a> for which we have won a prize of 700€ for best "Implementation and Feasibility"</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/LiquidFun/adventofcode">Six years of advent of code</a>, in five different programming languages</li>
        <li>Multiple machine learning competitions on Kaggle, including co-organizing the data science club at the University of Rostock</li>
      </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>This website</h2>
    <p>
      This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>,
      styled with <a href="https://tailwindcss.com">Tailwind CSS</a>, and
      uses vanilla TypeScript for all interactivity. The yarn ball following
      your cursor is rendered on a canvas using Verlet rope physics. If you
      enable attacker mode and monsters will fly at you — defend yourself
      with the yarn ball. Can you reach a high score?
    </p>
    <p>
      The source code is available on <a href="https://github.com/LiquidFun/brutenis.net">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
